Package: valkey-fractalsql
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends:
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends},
 libc6 (>= 2.38),
 valkey-server
Description: Stochastic Fractal Search module for Valkey
 valkey-fractalsql is a native C module for Valkey 7.2 / 8.0 / 8.1
 that exposes a FRACTAL.SEARCH command backed by a LuaJIT-compiled
 Stochastic Fractal Search optimizer. Built against Valkey's
 self-contained redismodule.h — the module ABI (REDISMODULE_APIVER_1,
 aliased as VALKEYMODULE_APIVER_1) was preserved across the April
 2024 fork from Redis, so one .so per arch covers every currently-
 shipping Valkey major.
 .
 The command is flagged readonly / fast / allow-stale so the Valkey
 8.x scheduler can dispatch it to an I/O worker thread, bypassing the
 main event loop for high throughput. LuaJIT is statically linked
 into the module; the only runtime dependency is glibc.
 .
 After installation, enable the module by adding the following line
 to valkey.conf (the post-install script prints this):
 .
     loadmodule /usr/lib/valkey/modules/fractalsql.so
 .
 An example config snippet is installed at
 /etc/valkey/modules-available/fractalsql.conf.
